/p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:14:"Editorial Team";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:16513:"<p>Are you looking for the best WordPress plugins for web developers? Many code lovers have their own set of preferred tools; however, when it comes to WordPress, the right set of plugins can make web development a snap. There are certain plugins that are a must-have for any web developers toolbox.</p>\n<p>In this article, we’ll share the 10 best WordPress plugins for web developers that you just can’t live without.</p>\n<h3><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/updraftplus/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">1. UpdraftPlus</a></h3>\n<p><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/updraftplus/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><img src="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/UpdraftPlus-1.jpg" alt="Updraft Plus" width="775" height="287" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-223329" srcset="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/UpdraftPlus-1.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/UpdraftPlus-1-300x111.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/UpdraftPlus-1-768x284.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px" /></a></p>\n<p>UpdraftPlus is an excellent plugin for those who want to make sure they&#8217;ll never lose their progress after making major changes to their website. This plugin makes it easy to <a href="https://www.isitwp.com/best-wordpress-backup-plugins-compared/">back up your website</a> to various programs, including Dropbox, Rackspace Cloud, Amazon S3, and even Google Drive.</p>\n<p>Right now, this plugin has over one million active users. Developers praise the ease of access, as well as the great features that other programs don’t offer. There’s a function that allows you to go in and set a schedule so you know you’ll always have a stable, safe backup of your priceless WordPress website.</p>\n<p>Considering that hackers are always trying to find their way into big-name websites, it certainly couldn’t hurt to have a full-fledged copy of your page elsewhere in case of an emergency.</p>\n<p><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/updraftplus/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Get Started with UpdraftPlus Today!</a></p>\n<h3><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/sucuri/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">2. Sucuri</a></h3>\n<p><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/sucuri/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><img src="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Sucuri-2.jpg" alt="Sucuri" width="775" height="287" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-223328" srcset="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Sucuri-2.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Sucuri-2-300x111.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Sucuri-2-768x284.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px" /></a></p>\n<p>Most people have an antivirus/anti-malware application on their desktop, so why wouldn’t you have a <a href="https://www.isitwp.com/best-wordpress-security-plugins-compared/">security plugin</a> protecting your website? Developers are using the Sucuri plugin to protect their websites from the most vile people and programs on the internet.</p>\n<p>Sucuri specializes in WordPress security and their plugin comes with a wide range of features, making it invaluable for everyone from the casual blogger to the multi-million dollar website developer.</p>\n<p>Upon installing this plugin, you’ll be greeted with a massive array of options including a malware scanner, real-time security watch, blacklisting watch, and access to a high-end firewall with the premium version. These are just some of the excellent features included with this plugin. You’ll also have access to post-hack security options in case you download it after you’ve already been attacked.</p>\n<p><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/sucuri/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Get Started with Sucuri Today!</a></p>\n<h3><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/css-hero/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">3. CSS Hero</a></h3>\n<p><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/css-hero/ " target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><img src="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/CSShero.png" alt="CSS hero" width="775" height="399" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-223327" srcset="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/CSShero.png 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/CSShero-300x154.png 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/CSShero-768x395.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px" /></a></p>\n<p>CSS Hero is a WordPress plugin that gives developers access to all the tools they need to customize their websites. It takes the complicated process of writing code and provides you with all of the tools and resources you need to edit your page in real time.</p>\n<p>The most notable feature of this plugin is it allows you to do custom work for individual devices. Normally, WordPress will adjust your site for the best fit based on the device being used. CSS Hero allows you to code your desktop, tablet, and mobile appearance to all look different, without the styles and changes overlapping and causing errors.</p>\n<p><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/css-hero/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Get Started with CSS Hero Today!</a></p>\n<h3><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/debug-bar/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">4. Debug Bar</a></h3>\n<p><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/debug-bar/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><img src="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/debug-bar.png" alt="debug bar" width="775" height="244" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-223326" srcset="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/debug-bar.png 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/debug-bar-300x94.png 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/debug-bar-768x242.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px" /></a></p>\n<p>The Debug Bar is a small-but-mighty tool for all serious developers. Instead of cycling through all your work looking for PHP notices and warnings, you can install this easy-to-use plugin instead.</p>\n<p>Once you get the Debug Bar on your WordPress site, it’ll appear on your admin bar. A quick glance will give you a whole host of valuable information. You’ll be able to identify cache options, as well as issues from within the database.</p>\n<p>Finally, you can attach add-ons to the Debug Tool to gain more insight. You can learn about your shortcodes, filters, registered post types, and much more!</p>\n<p><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/debug-bar/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Get Started with Debug Bar Today!</a></p>\n<h3><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/health-check/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">5. Health Check</a></h3>\n<p><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/health-check/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><img src="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/health-check.png" alt="health check" width="775" height="313" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-223325" srcset="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/health-check.png 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/health-check-300x121.png 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/health-check-768x310.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px" /></a></p>\n<p>The next tool, Health Check, is not for the novice WordPress user. Once installed, this plugin runs a full check on your system and configurations.</p>\n<p>You’ll be able to see information about your PHP and MySQL versions for updates and errors. Furthermore, it’ll run through your website from front to back so you’ll be able to see any issues in the debugging section of this plugin.</p>\n<p>Finally, this tool has a troubleshooting feature that lets you run your website in “vanilla WordPress.” In other words, you’ll start with your page in a bare-bones format and then you can slowly add code, plugins, and more behind the scenes. This gives you the ability to experiment with different combinations to see if there’s anything conflicting on your site. The troubleshooter helps you pick out what’s causing you problems, and allows you to build your website effectively.</p>\n<p><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/health-check/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Get Started with Health Check Today!</a></p>\n<h3><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/theme-check/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">6. Theme Check</a></h3>\n<p><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/theme-check/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><img src="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/theme-check.png" alt="theme check" width="775" height="254" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-223324" srcset="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/theme-check.png 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/theme-check-300x98.png 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/theme-check-768x252.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px" /></a></p>\n<p>Are you the type of developer who likes to regularly check to make sure that everything you’re doing follows the strict, specific standards set up by WordPress? If so, the Theme Check plugin is the perfect addition to your current WP plugin list.</p>\n<p>In a nutshell, Theme Check is an easy-to-install, easy-to-use plugin that allows you to run your current WordPress theme through automatic testing tools. The scanner determines whether or not your current theme falls in line with the latest WordPress standards.</p>\n<p>If there’re issues, they’ll pop up on a report after the scanner is done. You can go in, fix the errors, and run the scanner again to make sure everything is in working order.</p>\n<p><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/theme-check/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Get Started with Theme Check Today!</a></p>\n<h3><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/query-monitor/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">7. Query Monitor</a></h3>\n<p><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/query-monitor/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><img src="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/query-monitor.png" alt="query monitor" width="775" height="328" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-223323" srcset="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/query-monitor.png 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/query-monitor-300x127.png 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/query-monitor-768x325.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px" /></a></p>\n<p>Query Monitor is another excellent debugging plugin for your WordPress site. This tool is slightly more advanced than the previously-mentioned Debug Bar.</p>\n<p>The primary reason you’ll want to use this plugin is if you work with AJAX calls and REST API requests. Once you activate the plugin, you’ll see a list of all database queries. You can use this information to find out if other plugins, themes, or add-ons are malfunctioning.</p>\n<p>You’ll have access to a full datasheet showing you what’s working well, and what needs improvement. It may take some trial and error, but you’ll be able to debug your WordPress site and have it working smoothly again in no time!</p>\n<p><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/query-monitor/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Get Started with Query Monitor Today!</a></p>\n<h3><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/styleguide/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">8. StyleGuide</a></h3>\n<p><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/styleguide/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><img src="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/style-guide.png" alt="style guide" width="775" height="300" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-223322" srcset="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/style-guide.png 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/style-guide-300x116.png 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/style-guide-768x297.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px" /></a></p>\n<p>If you’re looking for a way to design custom fonts and colors for your WordPress website, look no further than the StyleGuide plugin.<br />\nAfter installing this plugin, you’ll be able to go through and customize every text aspect of your WP site. You’ll find 45 of the most popular Google Fonts that you can mix and match at your leisure.</p>\n<p>What cements StyleGuide onto our list of the best WordPress plugins for web developers is the fact that it works perfectly with all <a href="https://www.isitwp.com/top-wordpress-themes/">WordPress themes</a>. Once you find a theme you like, open up StyleGuide and tweak the fonts and colors until you have your one-of-a-kind website ready to be published. You can even view your changes in a live preview mode to ensure that you like the changes you’re making.</p>\n<p><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/styleguide/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Get Started with StyleGuide Today!</a></p>\n<h3><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/user-switching/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">9. User Switching</a></h3>\n<p><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/user-switching/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><img src="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/user-switching.png" alt="user switching" width="775" height="240" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-223321" srcset="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/user-switching.png 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/user-switching-300x93.png 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/user-switching-768x238.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px" /></a></p>\n<p>The User Switching plugin is the perfect addition to your WordPress site if you have multiple user accounts you frequently switch between. The plugin can be installed and ready to use in seconds.</p>\n<p>Once you have it up and running, you can freely switch between your registered users in seconds. You don’t have to worry about putting your security on the line either. During the switching process, there are no passwords revealed for any of the accounts.</p>\n<p>Furthermore, only those who have full admin access to your WordPress account can use the plugin. If there are other users who have limited accounts, they’ll not have access to this tool.</p>\n<p><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/user-switching/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Get Started with User Switching Today!</a></p>\n<h3><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/log-deprecated-notices/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">10. Log Deprecated Notices</a></h3>\n<p><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/log-deprecated-notices/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><img src="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Log-Deprecated-Notices.png" alt="Log Deprecated Notices" width="775" height="212" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-223320" srcset="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Log-Deprecated-Notices.png 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Log-Deprecated-Notices-300x82.png 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Log-Deprecated-Notices-768x210.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px" /></a></p>\n<p>The final developer plugin we&#8217;ll look at today is called Log Deprecated Notices. Essentially, this plugin is used in combination with the WP_DEBUG plugin to locate deprecated files and functions.</p>\n<p>You can easily go in and look at the list of deprecated files and find out if there&#8217;s an easy solution for these issues. The Debug tool helps the base plugin work more effectively as it tracks down errors that may otherwise get overlooked.</p>\n<p>The most common reason people download this tool is if they&#8217;re looking to clean up files, or if they have outdated themes or plugins on their website. It keeps your page up to snuff on all of the latest WordPress practices and detailed coding guides.</p>\n<p><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/log-deprecated-notices/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Get Started with Log Deprecated Notices Today!</a></p>\n<p>We hope this article helped you discover the best WordPress plugins for web developers!</p>\n<p>If you liked this article, you might also enjoy our list of the <a href="https://www.isitwp.com/best-wordpress-caching-plugins-compared/">best WordPress caching plugins</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.isitwp.com/best-wordpress-plugins-web-developers/">10 Best WordPress Plugins for Web Developers (Compared)</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.isitwp.com">IsItWP - WordPress Technology Lookup Tool</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:66:"https://www.isitwp.com/best-wordpress-plugins-web-developers/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:51:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:57:"How to Save Partial Form Data in WordPress (Step by Step)";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:59:"https://www.isitwp.com/save-partial-entries-wordpress-form/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:67:"https://www.isitwp.com/save-partial-entries-wordpress-form/#respond";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Mon, 26 Nov 2018 12:45:24 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:19:"WordPress Tutorials";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12:"contact form";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:16:"lead abandonment";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7:"wpforms";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:32:"https://www.isitwp.com/?p=224192";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:611:"<p>Do you want to save partial entries of your WordPress form? We understand. There are few things more frustrating than losing a customer due to an abandoned order form, or a potential client exiting your contact form. That’s why, in this article, we’ll show you how to save partial data of your WordPress form. Get [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.isitwp.com/save-partial-entries-wordpress-form/">How to Save Partial Form Data in WordPress (Step by Step)</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.isitwp.com">IsItWP - WordPress Technology Lookup Tool</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:14:"Editorial Team";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6197:"<p>Do you want to save partial entries of your WordPress form? We understand. There are few things more frustrating than losing a customer due to an abandoned order form, or a potential client exiting your contact form.</p>\n<p>That’s why, in this article, we’ll show you how to save partial data of your WordPress form. Get ready to finally capture those missed leads!</p>\n<h3>Saving Partial Form Entries with WPForms</h3>\n<p>Abandoned forms happen most often with order forms, support request forms, price quote request forms, and basic contact forms. However, no matter which form is abandoned by a user, it’s painful for you as a site owner.</p>\n<p>Those potential customers have left, and will likely never return again.</p>\n<p>Unfortunately, not all <a href="https://www.isitwp.com/best-wordpress-contact-form-plugins/" title="7 Best WordPress Contact Form Plugins Compared (2018)">contact form plugins</a> are created equal. If you’re lucky, you’ll find one that lets you build the forms you want (like an order form, for example); but, there’s a slim chance it’ll let you capture those exiting leads.</p>\n<p>The good news is: <a href="https://wpforms.com" target="_blank">WPForms</a> does.</p>\n<p><a href="https://wpforms.com" target="_blank"><img src="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/wpforms.png" alt="wpforms" width="775" height="350" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-223885" srcset="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/wpforms.png 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/wpforms-300x135.png 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/wpforms-768x347.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px" /></a></p>\n<p>Not only does <a href="https://wpforms.com" target="_blank">WPForms</a> let you build an infinite variety of forms, it also has a <strong>Form Abandonment addon</strong> that allows you to follow up with potential customers, even if they abandoned your form before completing it!</p>\n<p>In other words, the Form Abandonment addon allows you to save partial entries of your WordPress form.</p>\n<p>Even better news? IsItWP readers can get 10 percent off the price of <a href="https://wpforms.com" target="_blank">WPForms</a> by entering in the coupon code <strong>SAVE10</strong>.</p>\n<p>Once you have <a href="https://wpforms.com" target="_blank">WPForms</a> downloaded, installed, and activated, move onto the next step to learn how to save partial data of your WordPress form.</p>\n<h3>Step 1: Activate the Addon</h3>\n<p>From your WordPress dashboard, head to <strong>WPForms » Addons</strong>.</p>\n<p>Then, scroll down until you see the <strong>Form Abandonment</strong> addon. Click <strong>Install</strong>. Then, click the <strong>Activate</strong> toggle. When it turns green, that means you did it right.</p>\n<p><img src="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/form-abandonment-addon.png" alt="form abandonment addon" width="600" height="378" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-224195" srcset="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/form-abandonment-addon.png 600w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/form-abandonment-addon-300x189.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></p>\n<p>All set? Time for the next step!</p>\n<h3>Step 2: Create a Form</h3>\n<p>Since WPForms has an infinite variety of forms you can create, it would be nearly impossible for us to cover how to build the exact form you want in this humble article.</p>\n<p>However, we do have several posts that may help:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/add-contact-form-wordpress-website/">How to Create a Contact Form</a></li>\n<li><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/create-multi-page-form-wordpress/">How to Create a Multi-Page Form</a></li>\n<li><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/create-wordpress-donation-form/">How to Create a Donation Form</a></li>\n<li><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/custom-user-registration-form-wordpress/">How to Create a Custom User Registration Form</a></li>\n<li><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/create-job-application-form-wordpress/">How to Create a Job Application Form</a></li>\n<li><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/create-a-survey-in-wordpress/">How to Create a Survey Form</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>After you’ve created your perfect form, don’t forget to click <strong>Save</strong>. Then, head onto the next step to learn how to save partial WordPress form submission.</p>\n<h3>Step 3: Enable Your Form Abandonment Settings</h3>\n<p>While still in the WPForms editor, head to <strong>Settings » Form Abandonment</strong>.</p>\n<p>Then, simply check the box that says <strong>Enable Form Abandonment Lead Capture</strong>.</p>\n<p><img src="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/form-abandonment.png" alt="form abandonment" width="775" height="217" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-224196" srcset="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/form-abandonment.png 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/form-abandonment-300x84.png 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/form-abandonment-768x215.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px" /></p>\n<p>That’s it! You’re done!</p>\n<p>Now, whenever someone fills out a few fields of your form and then exits, WPForms will save their information in your form entries.</p>\n<p>Thanks to this handy addon, you’ll be able to reach out to those lost leads and ask them if they REALLY meant to leave your site. Don’t be shy! Remind them why you’re great, and turn those abandoning leads into full-fledged conversions.</p>\n<p>We hope this article helped you learn how to save partial entries of your WordPress form.</p>\n<p>If you enjoyed this post, you might also like our in-depth comparison of the <a href="https://www.isitwp.com/best-email-marketing-services-compared/" title="9 Best Email Marketing Services Compared (2018)">best email marketing services</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.isitwp.com/save-partial-entries-wordpress-form/">How to Save Partial Form Data in WordPress (Step by Step)</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.isitwp.com">IsItWP - WordPress Technology Lookup Tool</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:64:"https://www.isitwp.com/save-partial-entries-wordpress-form/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:39:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:6:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:58:"BirchPress Review – WordPress Appointment Booking Plugin";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:52:"https://www.isitwp.com/wordpress-plugins/birchpress/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:60:"https://www.isitwp.com/wordpress-plugins/birchpress/#respond";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Fri, 23 Nov 2018 12:53:25 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:56:"https://www.isitwp.com/?post_type=isitwp_plugin&p=224894";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:621:"<p>Want to add an online booking system on your WordPress site? BirchPress is one of the most popular, user-friendly WordPress appointment and booking plugins available on the market. But is it the best choice for you? In this BirchPress review, we’ll take a look at its features, functionalities, pricing, and more to help you decide [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.isitwp.com/wordpress-plugins/birchpress/">BirchPress Review – WordPress Appointment Booking Plugin</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.isitwp.com">IsItWP - WordPress Technology Lookup Tool</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:14:"Editorial Team";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:15331:"<p>Want to add an online booking system on your WordPress site? <a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/birchpress/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">BirchPress</a> is one of the most popular, user-friendly <a href="https://www.isitwp.com/best-wordpress-booking-plugins-compared/">WordPress appointment and booking plugins</a> available on the market. But is it the best choice for you? </p>\n<p>In this BirchPress review, we’ll take a look at its features, functionalities, pricing, and more to help you decide if it’s the right option for you. </p>\n<h3>About BirchPress Plugin</h3>\n<p><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/birchpress/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><img src="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/birchpress-wordpress-plugin.jpg" alt="birchpress-wordpress-plugin" width="775" height="350" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-221491" srcset="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/birchpress-wordpress-plugin.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/birchpress-wordpress-plugin-300x135.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/birchpress-wordpress-plugin-768x347.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px" /></a></p>\n<p><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/birchpress/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">BirchPress</a> is a highly comprehensive WordPress appointment booking plugin. It allows you to create easy online appointment forms on your <a href="https://www.isitwp.com/how-to-make-a-website-step-by-step/">WordPress site</a> so your visitors can check availability, book appointments, or make reservations online. It’s a perfect scheduler plugin that allows your users to easily make appointments on your site without your direct involvement. </p>\n<p>The plugin syncs your booking calendar with the other calendars you already use like Google Calendar, iCal, iPhone, Android, or Outlook. You can configure and send email notifications and reminders to your users when the appointments are booked, rescheduled, or canceled. </p>\n<p>It has inbuilt PayPal and credit card support for accepting payments. If you want to use other payment gateways, you can add them through WooCommerce integration.  </p>\n<p>BirchPress is suitable for all types of businesses that allow online appointment options. You can use it for health and wellness, education, fitness, recreation, salon, beauty, automobile, or any other type of business or service website. </p>\n<h3>BirchPress Review – Getting Started with BirchPress</h3>\n<p><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/birchpress/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">BirchPress</a> comes with a simple and clean user interface that enables you to add appointment booking forms easily on your WordPress posts and pages. </p>\n<p>First, you’ll need to install and activate the BirchPress plugin on your site. Then, go to <strong>Appointments &raquo; Settings</strong> to configure the plugin settings. </p>\n<p><img src="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/general-settings.png" alt="general settings- appointment booking" width="740" height="520" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-221362" srcset="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/general-settings.png 740w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/general-settings-300x211.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 740px) 100vw, 740px" /></p>\n<p>In the <strong>General</strong> tab, you can configure your time zone, date and time format, currency, and booking preferences. You can also insert your plugin support license key from there. </p>\n<p>Next, <strong>Form Builder</strong> allows you to customize your appointments. The plugin has a pre-designed appointment form ready for you, so you can skip the Form Builder settings if you prefer using the default form. </p>\n<p>The <strong>Notifications</strong> tab allows you to configure notification emails to your service providers and clients. </p>\n<p>You can add your PayPal email and set up payment options from the <strong>Payments</strong> tab. If you want to use WooCommerce, you can enable and set it up from the <strong>WooCommerce</strong> tab. If you want to add custom code, you can do that from the <strong>Custom Code</strong> tab. </p>\n<p>Once you review and configure all the plugin settings, you can go ahead and add <strong>locations</strong>, <strong>service providers</strong>, and <strong>services</strong>. </p>\n<h3>Adding Locations, Providers, and Services</h3>\n<p>The <a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/birchpress/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">BirchPress plugin</a> makes it easy to build a complete appointment booking system in WordPress with options to add different locations, providers, and services. </p>\n<p>First, you can add the different locations where you’re providing services from. To add a new location, go to <strong>Appointments &raquo; Locations</strong> and click <strong>Add Location</strong>. </p>\n<p><img src="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/birchpress-plugin-add-new-location.jpg" alt="birchpress-plugin-add-new-location" width="775" height="550" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-224904" srcset="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/birchpress-plugin-add-new-location.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/birchpress-plugin-add-new-location-300x213.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/birchpress-plugin-add-new-location-768x545.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px" /></p>\n<p>Next, you can add different service providers. Service providers can be different agencies or different individuals in an agency. For example, if you’re creating a booking form for a hospital, you’ll need to add each doctor as a service provider.  </p>\n<p>To add a new provider, go to <strong>Appointments &raquo; Providers</strong> and click <strong>Add Provider</strong>. </p>\n<p><img src="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/add-new-provider-birchpress-plugin.jpg" alt="add-new-provider-birchpress-plugin" width="775" height="272" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-224905" srcset="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/add-new-provider-birchpress-plugin.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/add-new-provider-birchpress-plugin-300x105.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/add-new-provider-birchpress-plugin-768x270.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px" /></p>\n<p>Enter the service provider name and description. Choose a calendar color. </p>\n<p>Then, scroll down to <strong>Additional Info</strong> and enter the service provider’s email address. This feature is available only in the premium versions of the plugin. </p>\n<p>After that, scroll down to the <strong>Work Schedule</strong> section. Then, select a location and click <strong>Add Schedule</strong> to set up the available times. If the provider’s services are available in multiple locations, you can set that up one-by-one. </p>\n<p><img src="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/work-schedule-birchpress.jpg" alt="work-schedule-birchpress" width="775" height="380" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-224906" srcset="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/work-schedule-birchpress.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/work-schedule-birchpress-300x147.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/work-schedule-birchpress-768x377.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px" /></p>\n<p>Once you set up everything, go ahead and publish the provider. </p>\n<p>Next, you’ll need to add Services. Go to <strong>Appointments &raquo; Services</strong> and click the <strong>Add Service</strong> button. </p>\n<p><img src="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/add-services-birchpress.jpg" alt="add-services-birchpress" width="775" height="415" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-224907" srcset="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/add-services-birchpress.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/add-services-birchpress-300x161.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/add-services-birchpress-768x411.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px" /></p>\n<p>Enter your service name and description. Then, choose service locations, and service providers from the right side panel. </p>\n<p>Then, scroll down to the <strong>Service Settings</strong> section and configure your service options. </p>\n<p><img src="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/service-settings.png" alt="service settings" width="752" height="465" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-221355" srcset="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/service-settings.png 752w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/service-settings-300x186.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 752px) 100vw, 752px" /></p>\n<p>Then, go ahead and publish your services. </p>\n<p>Now that you’ve added locations, providers, and services, you’re all set to add an appointment form on your site. </p>\n<h3>Adding Appointment Booking Form on Your Site</h3>\n<p>Adding booking form with <a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/birchpress/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">BirchPress</a> is easy thanks to shortcodes. All you need to do is to open the page you want to add the booking form to and paste the shortcode below:</p>\n<p><strong>[bpscheduler_booking_form]</strong></p>\n<p><img src="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/create-booking-page-birchpress.jpg" alt="create-booking-page-birchpress" width="775" height="320" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-224909" srcset="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/create-booking-page-birchpress.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/create-booking-page-birchpress-300x124.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/create-booking-page-birchpress-768x317.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px" /></p>\n<p>Then, publish the page. You can now view the page in the front-end. The appointment form looks like the screenshot below: </p>\n<p><img src="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/appointment-form-birchpress.jpg" alt="appointment-form-birchpress" width="428" height="594" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-224910" srcset="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/appointment-form-birchpress.jpg 428w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/appointment-form-birchpress-216x300.jpg 216w" sizes="(max-width: 428px) 100vw, 428px" /></p>\n<h3>Viewing Appointments on Your Calender</h3>\n<p>Once people start booking appointments on your site, you can view them on your dashboard. Go to <strong>Appointments &raquo; Calendar</strong>. </p>\n<p><img src="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/calendar-birchpress.png" alt="calendar birchpress" width="740" height="420" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-221361" srcset="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/calendar-birchpress.png 740w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/calendar-birchpress-300x170.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 740px) 100vw, 740px" /></p>\n<p>BirchPress also allows you to display your calendar on your website front-end for your users to view publicly. To add a public calendar, you can insert the following shortcode to a page where you want to show your calendar: </p>\n<p><strong>[bpscheduler_public_calendar]</strong></p>\n<p><img src="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/add-public-calendar-birchpress.jpg" alt="add-public-calendar-birchpress" width="775" height="320" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-224912" srcset="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/add-public-calendar-birchpress.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/add-public-calendar-birchpress-300x124.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/add-public-calendar-birchpress-768x317.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px" /></p>\n<p>This feature is available only in the <strong>Business</strong> and <strong>Business+</strong> plans. </p>\n<h3>BirchPress Plugin: Pricing and Support</h3>\n<p>BirchPress is a free and premium WordPress plugin. You can find its free edition in the official WordPress plugin repository. However, it has a limited set of features. To enjoy all of its features, you’ll need to buy a premium plan. </p>\n<p>There’re 3 pricing plans: <strong>Personal</strong>, <strong>Business</strong>, and <strong>Business+</strong>. </p>\n<p><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/birchpress/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><img src="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/pricing-birchpress-review.jpg" alt="pricing-birchpress-review" width="775" height="445" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-224913" srcset="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/pricing-birchpress-review.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/pricing-birchpress-review-300x172.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/pricing-birchpress-review-768x441.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px" /></a></p>\n<p>With the <strong>Personal</strong> plan, you’ll be able to use automated email notifications, send reminder emails, and block holidays; however, it misses out on payment options. The Personal plan costs $99. </p>\n<p>If you want to accept payments for the online reservations your users make, you’ll need to buy the <strong>Business</strong> or <strong>Business+</strong> plan. With the Business plan, you&#8217;ll get only PayPal integration; but the Business+ plan also lets you use Authorize.net and WooCommerce. </p>\n<p>All of the 3 plans offer 1 site license and 1 year of support and updates. </p>\n<p>For support, you can visit the <a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/birchpress/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">official BirchPress website</a> and go to the <strong>Support &raquo; Documentation</strong> menu. It has a complete set of articles to help you configure and use the plugin. </p>\n<h3>Our Verdict on Using BirchPress for WordPress Booking System</h3>\n<p>BirchPress is a user-friendly and feature-rich WordPress appointment booking plugin. It offers a simple interface for adding your services, service locations, and providers. It enables your users to book appointments for different services in different locations with different providers in a hassle-free way. </p>\n<p>Adding an appointment form on your site is made easy with shortcodes. With BirchPress&#8217; premium plans, you can accept payments, configure your email notifications, customize your appointment forms, set up a public calendar, and more. The plugin has all the features you’ll ever need in a WordPress booking system. </p>\n<p>We believe that <a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/birchpress/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">BirchPress</a> is the best WordPress appointment and booking plugin. It’s perfect for any WordPress user who want to add an online booking system on their sites. </p>\n<p>We give it 4.5 out of 5 stars. Here’s the breakdown of our review score:</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.isitwp.com/wordpress-plugins/birchpress/">BirchPress Review – WordPress Appointment Booking Plugin</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.isitwp.com">IsItWP - WordPress Technology Lookup Tool</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:57:"https://www.isitwp.com/wordpress-plugins/birchpress/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:51:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:55:"20 Best WordPress Church Themes for Expanding the Flock";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:54:"https://www.isitwp.com/best-wordpress-themes-churches/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:62:"https://www.isitwp.com/best-wordpress-themes-churches/#respond";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Thu, 22 Nov 2018 11:30:21 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"Resources";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:21:"best wordpress themes";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:14:"premium themes";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:17:"responsive themes";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:32:"https://www.isitwp.com/?p=223796";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:618:"<p>Are you looking for the best WordPress themes for churches? The perfect theme can turn your church’s website into a follower-generating machine. In this article, we’ll share the 20 best church themes for WordPress. All of them are responsive, so they’ll look perfect on any device. 1. Maranatha If you want to start a website [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.isitwp.com/best-wordpress-themes-churches/">20 Best WordPress Church Themes for Expanding the Flock</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.isitwp.com">IsItWP - WordPress Technology Lookup Tool</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:14:"Editorial Team";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:25255:"<p>Are you looking for the best WordPress themes for churches? The perfect theme can turn your church’s website into a follower-generating machine.</p>\n<p>In this article, we’ll share the 20 best church themes for WordPress. All of them are responsive, so they’ll look perfect on any device.</p>\n<h3><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/churchthemes-maranatha/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">1. Maranatha</a></h3>\n<p><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/churchthemes-maranatha/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><img src="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Maranatha.png" alt="Maranatha" width="775" height="322" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-223815" srcset="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Maranatha.png 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Maranatha-300x125.png 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Maranatha-768x319.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px" /></a></p>\n<p>If you want to <a href="https://www.isitwp.com/how-to-make-a-website-step-by-step/" title="How to Make a Website in 2018- Step by Step (with Pictures)">start a website</a> that includes innovative features, like parallax-inspired scrolling on the homepage, then Maranatha is a great theme to use.</p>\n<p>You can use a still image or a video as your homepage background to entice new followers to your flock. And your most important pages will always be a mere click away thanks to the sticky menu that “sticks” to the top of the screen, even as your site’s visitors scroll downward.</p>\n<p>With Maranatha, you can upload your sermons as audio or video files, or even type out the transcriptions as text posts for your blog. This theme also offers beautiful layout options for your About page and Events calendar.</p>\n<p><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/churchthemes-maranatha/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Get Started with Maranatha Today!</a></p>\n<h3><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/studiopress-outreach-pro/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">2. Outreach Pro</a></h3>\n<p><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/studiopress-outreach-pro/ " target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><img src="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/outreach-pro.jpg" alt="outreach pro" width="775" height="373" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-223816" srcset="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/outreach-pro.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/outreach-pro-300x144.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/outreach-pro-768x370.jpg 768w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/outreach-pro-330x160.jpg 330w" sizes="(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px" /></a></p>\n<p>Brought to you by the fine folks at StudioPress, Outreach Pro utilizes their powerful Genesis framework. If you need to convey a lot of information on your website, this is a great theme to pick.</p>\n<p>There are several pre-made templates to get your site up-and-running in a hurry. And the theme’s customizer allows you to alter the color scheme to match your church’s brand.</p>\n<p>With 12 widget areas and a customizable header, you’ll have no trouble tweaking Outreach Pro to look exactly how you need it to.</p>\n<p><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/studiopress-outreach-pro/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Get Started with Outreach Pro Today!</a></p>\n<h3><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/mythemeshop-salvation/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">3. Salvation</a></h3>\n<p><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/mythemeshop-salvation/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><img src="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Salvation.png" alt="Salvation" width="775" height="328" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-223817" srcset="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Salvation.png 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Salvation-300x127.png 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Salvation-768x325.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px" /></a></p>\n<p>Clean, elegant, and softly pink like a Heavenly sunrise. The Salvation theme is perfect for a number of denominations to get their faith-based messages across in a beautiful way.</p>\n<p>This theme comes with an event management system and a tasteful donation form that integrates with PayPal. Plus, there are several custom widgets you can use to make the most of your website.</p>\n<p><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/mythemeshop-salvation/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Get Started with Salvation Today!</a></p>\n<h3><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/churchthemes-exodus/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">4. Exodus</a></h3>\n<p><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/churchthemes-exodus/ " target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><img src="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Exodus.png" alt="Exodus" width="775" height="323" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-223818" srcset="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Exodus.png 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Exodus-300x125.png 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Exodus-768x320.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px" /></a></p>\n<p>Don’t let the name fool you! Although “exodus” typically means a mass departure of people, the last thing your site visitors will want to do when they land on your webpage is leave. The Exodus theme will have believers rushing to your flock.</p>\n<p>Exodus is easily customizable, and uses a live preview function so that you can view your changes to its colors and fonts in real time.</p>\n<p>This theme includes pages already built-in for Sermons, Events, Locations, and Staff Profiles. We were especially impressed with the Sermons page as it allows you to upload your messages as text, audio, or video files.</p>\n<p><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/churchthemes-exodus/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Get Started with Exodus Today!</a></p>\n<h3><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/churchthemes-resurrect/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">5. Resurrect</a></h3>\n<p><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/churchthemes-resurrect/ " target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><img src="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Resurrect.png" alt="Resurrect" width="775" height="293" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-223819" srcset="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Resurrect.png 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Resurrect-300x113.png 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Resurrect-768x290.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px" /></a></p>\n<p>Bring fresh live to your church’s website with the Resurrect theme! Choose from a light or dark color scheme, and then customize it to your heart’s content.</p>\n<p>Resurrect comes with several fonts to choose from and the option to upload a custom logo image. It’s also optimized for high-resolution screens, so your images will look crisp on every device.</p>\n<p><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/churchthemes-resurrect/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Get Started with Resurrect Today!</a></p>\n<h3><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/upthemes-one-church/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">6. One Church</a></h3>\n<p><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/upthemes-one-church/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><img src="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/one-church.jpg" alt="one church" width="775" height="339" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-223820" srcset="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/one-church.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/one-church-300x131.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/one-church-768x336.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px" /></a></p>\n<p>One Church features 12 different color schemes to choose from. Don’t like any of the colors provided? Not a problem. They also include a custom color picker so you can choose your own!</p>\n<p>You can publish your sermons in video, audio, or text formats. And the page categories lets you list them by speaker, topic, or series.</p>\n<p>One Church is also integrated with Adobe Typekit so you’ll have plenty of font options to choose from to make your site stand out from the crowd.</p>\n<p><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/upthemes-one-church/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Get Started with One Church Today!</a></p>\n<h3><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/cssigniter-prayer/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">7. Prayer</a></h3>\n<p><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/cssigniter-prayer/ " target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><img src="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Prayer.png" alt="Prayer" width="775" height="295" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-223821" srcset="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Prayer.png 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Prayer-300x114.png 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Prayer-768x292.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px" /></a></p>\n<p>With its flexible homepage layout, Prayer allows you to add multiple widgets to your front page to create a truly unique layout.  The featured gallery slider is a nice touch as well.</p>\n<p>If your church is active on social media, you’ll be very pleased with its social networking widget. You can connect your site to Instagram, Twitter, and more!</p>\n<p>Just as prayers come in many different forms, the Prayer theme comes in many different colors. Best of all? You can use a different color scheme for each page you create!</p>\n<p><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/cssigniter-prayer/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Get Started with Prayer Today!</a></p>\n<h3><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/organizedthemes-kerygma/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">8. Kerygma</a></h3>\n<p><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/organizedthemes-kerygma/ " target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><img src="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Kerygma.png" alt="Kerygma" width="775" height="279" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-223822" srcset="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Kerygma.png 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Kerygma-300x108.png 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Kerygma-768x276.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px" /></a></p>\n<p>If your church has a podcast, then Kerygma is the theme for you. It was made specifically to feature podcasts in audio or video form.</p>\n<p>It comes bundled with SiteOrigin, one of the <a href="https://www.isitwp.com/best-wordpress-page-builders-compared/" title="7 Best Drag and Drop WordPress Page Builders Compared (2018)">best website page builder plugins</a> on the market. You can use its drag and drop functionality to quickly and easily customize your site any way you like.</p>\n<p>With the option to upload your own logo, change the theme’s color scheme, and make use of over 600 Google fonts, you’ll be able to match your website to your brand with ease.</p>\n<p><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/organizedthemes-kerygma/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Get Started with Kerygma Today!</a></p>\n<h3><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/organizedthemes-epic/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">9. Epic</a></h3>\n<p><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/organizedthemes-epic/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><img src="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Epic.png" alt="Epic" width="595" height="250" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-223823" srcset="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Epic.png 595w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Epic-300x126.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 595px) 100vw, 595px" /></a></p>\n<p>This theme will make your website as epic as your church itself! Choose from a light or dark color scheme and get ready to impress.</p>\n<p>Another podcast-focused theme, Epic allows you to upload audio and video feeds for iTunes and RSS subscriptions. And the categories feature lets you archive each of your speakers separately.</p>\n<p>We liked that the navigation bar could be placed inside your logo or directly above it.</p>\n<p><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/organizedthemes-epic/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Get Started with Epic Today!</a></p>\n<h3><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/god-grace/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">10. God Grace</a></h3>\n<p><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/god-grace/ " target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><img src="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/God-Grace.png" alt="God Grace" width="500" height="252" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-223824" srcset="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/God-Grace.png 500w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/God-Grace-300x151.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /></a></p>\n<p>Fully-integrated with <a href="https://www.isitwp.com/wordpress-plugins/visual-composer/" title="WPBakery Page Builder Review (Formerly Visual Composer)">WPBakery</a>, God Grace is quick and easy to set up via an intuitive drag and drop builder. But this is just one of many reasons it made it onto our list of the best WordPress Church themes.</p>\n<p>God Grace guarantees full support from their team should you ever get stuck while building your website. They pride themselves on being fast and reliable.</p>\n<p>Share sermons, promote events, and accept donations through this incredible theme. You can even sell products, like church literature or branded clothing, thanks to its WooCommerce integration.</p>\n<p><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/god-grace/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Get Started with God Grace Today!</a></p>\n<h3><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/blessing/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">11. Blessing</a></h3>\n<p><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/blessing/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><img src="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Blessing.png" alt="Blessing" width="500" height="253" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-223825" srcset="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Blessing.png 500w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Blessing-300x152.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /></a></p>\n<p>Equipped with WPBakery and Revolution Slider, Blessing lives up to its name. You’ll certainly feel blessed by this easy-to-use church theme.</p>\n<p>The touch and swipe image carousel is perfect if you expect to have a lot of mobile or touchscreen visitors.</p>\n<p><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/blessing/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Get Started with Blessing Today!</a></p>\n<h3><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/holy-church/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">12. Holy Church</a></h3>\n<p><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/holy-church/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><img src="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Holy-Church.png" alt="Holy Church" width="500" height="252" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-223826" srcset="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Holy-Church.png 500w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Holy-Church-300x151.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /></a></p>\n<p>Perfect for churches and prayer groups, Holy Church comes loaded with everything you’ll need to make your website a success. This theme has a powerful blog which is great for sharing news updates with your followers.</p>\n<p>It comes with Events Calendar for showcasing upcoming events within your organization. It’s also compatible with WPBakery for ease-of-use and WooCommerce so you can sell things from your gift shop online.</p>\n<p><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/holy-church/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Get Started with Holy Church Today!</a></p>\n<h3><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/teslathemes-credo/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">13. Credo</a></h3>\n<p><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/teslathemes-credo/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><img src="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Credo.jpg" alt="Credo" width="655" height="282" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-223828" srcset="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Credo.jpg 655w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Credo-300x129.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 655px) 100vw, 655px" /></a></p>\n<p>Credo is perfect for churches of all denominations. It also works extremely well for charities and nonprofits.</p>\n<p>Archive your sermons, share photos and videos, get eyes on your upcoming events, and tell the world about your church!</p>\n<p><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/teslathemes-credo/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Get Started with Credo Today!</a></p>\n<h3><a href="https://wordpress.org/themes/charitize/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">14. Charitize</a></h3>\n<p><a href="https://wordpress.org/themes/charitize/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><img src="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Charitize.png" alt="Charitize" width="775" height="312" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-223829" srcset="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Charitize.png 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Charitize-300x121.png 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Charitize-768x309.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px" /></a></p>\n<p>Translation-ready with plenty of customization options, Charitize is perfect for your church or charity organization.</p>\n<p>They recommend using the <a href="https://www.isitwp.com/wordpress-plugins/jetpack/" title="Jetpack Review 2018 : Should You Use It? (Pros &#038; Cons)">Jetpack plugin</a> with this theme. If you happen to love Jetpack already, then this is a great choice!</p>\n<p><a href="https://wordpress.org/themes/charitize/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Get Started with Charitize Today!</a></p>\n<h3><a href="https://wordpress.org/themes/themoments/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">15. TheMoments</a></h3>\n<p><a href="https://wordpress.org/themes/themoments/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><img src="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/TheMoments.png" alt="TheMoments" width="775" height="230" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-223830" srcset="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/TheMoments.png 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/TheMoments-300x89.png 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/TheMoments-768x228.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px" /></a></p>\n<p>This free WordPress theme is very lightweight, making loading speed a priority. It’s also optimized for SEO so that you’ll rise through Google’s ranks.</p>\n<p>It supports WooCommerce so, if you have an online store, you’ll be good to go. We also enjoyed the Instagram widget, which is perfect if you already have a social media presence.</p>\n<p><a href="https://wordpress.org/themes/themoments/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Get Started with TheMoments Today!</a></p>\n<h3><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/church-and-events/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">16. Church and Events</a></h3>\n<p><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/church-and-events/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><img src="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/church-and-events.png" alt="church and events" width="590" height="300" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-223831" srcset="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/church-and-events.png 590w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/church-and-events-300x153.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px" /></a></p>\n<p>Do you have a church? Does your church host events? Then Church and Events is the theme for you.</p>\n<p>This theme supports  The Event Calendar Pro, Filter Bar, WooTickets, and Community Events plugins which makes it absolutely perfect for churches that host several events throughout the year.</p>\n<p>It also has 10 header options and 20 footer options, giving you plenty of customization options.</p>\n<p><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/church-and-events/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Get Started with Church and Events Today!</a></p>\n<h3><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/wp-church/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">17. WP-Church</a></h3>\n<p><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/wp-church/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><img src="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/WP-Church.png" alt="WP Church" width="775" height="241" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-223832" srcset="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/WP-Church.png 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/WP-Church-300x93.png 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/WP-Church-768x239.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px" /></a></p>\n<p>With its newsletter subscription widget, WP-Church was designed to help you skyrocket your <a href="https://www.isitwp.com/best-email-marketing-services-compared/" title="9 Best Email Marketing Services Compared (2018)">email subscribers</a>. And with its custom-built sermon gallery and eye-catching slideshow, you’ll be getting plenty of engagement on your webpage.</p>\n<p>With 6 custom colors to choose from and 8 custom widget areas, you’ll be able to make WP-Church look exactly how you want it to.</p>\n<p><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/wp-church/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Get Started with WP-Church Today!</a></p>\n<h3><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/dunamis/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">18. Dunamis</a></h3>\n<p><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/dunamis/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><img src="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Dunamis.png" alt="Dunamis" width="775" height="171" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-223833" srcset="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Dunamis.png 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Dunamis-300x66.png 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Dunamis-768x169.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px" /></a></p>\n<p>Give your religious movement a modern look with the Dunamis theme.</p>\n<p>Dunamis comes with a demo site that’s easy to install for quick website setup. Or, if you prefer, you can use its built-in drag and drop page builder to design your website from scratch.</p>\n<p>We were especially impressed with its donation management system. Accept donations on your website and then keep track of them with ease right from your admin dashboard!</p>\n<p><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/dunamis/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Get Started with Dunamis Today!</a></p>\n<h3><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/benedicto/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">19. Benedicto</a></h3>\n<p><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/benedicto/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><img src="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Benedicto.png" alt="Benedicto" width="500" height="275" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-223834" srcset="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Benedicto.png 500w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Benedicto-300x165.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /></a></p>\n<p>Benedicto features 9 custom page layouts, 35 custom widgets, and is completely translation-ready. If you’re looking to attract a diverse following, this is a fantastic choice.</p>\n<p>With unlimited color choices and font types, Benedicto can effortlessly conform to your brand. Plus, you can embed any sermons you’ve uploaded on Soundcloud.com!</p>\n<p><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/benedicto/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Get Started with Benedicto Today!</a></p>\n<h3><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/risen/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">20. Risen</a></h3>\n<p><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/risen/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><img src="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Risen.jpg" alt="Risen" width="600" height="305" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-223835" srcset="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Risen.jpg 600w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Risen-300x153.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></a></p>\n<p>Rise to new heights with the Risen theme! It has everything you could ever want in a WordPress church theme: a sermon archive, an events page, a photo gallery, a news page, and more.</p>\n<p>This theme is incredibly versatile and works well for churches of all denominations, charity groups, and nonprofit organizations.</p>\n<p><a href="https://www.isitwp.com/refer/risen/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Get Started with Risen Today!</a></p>\n<p>We hope this article helped you discover the best WordPress themes for churches.</p>\n<p>If you liked this post, you might also enjoy our easy step-by-step tutorial on <a href="https://www.isitwp.com/create-wordpress-donation-form/" title="How to Create a WordPress Donation Form (Step by Step)">how to build a donation form in WordPress</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.isitwp.com/best-wordpress-themes-churches/">20 Best WordPress Church Themes for Expanding the Flock</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.isitwp.com">IsItWP - WordPress Technology Lookup Tool</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:59:"https://www.isitwp.com/best-wordpress-themes-churches/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:39:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:6:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:49:"WP Mail SMTP Review: #1 SMTP Plugin for WordPress";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:54:"https://www.isitwp.com/wordpress-plugins/wp-mail-smtp/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:62:"https://www.isitwp.com/wordpress-plugins/wp-mail-smtp/#respond";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Wed, 21 Nov 2018 05:29:00 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:53:"https://www.isitwp.com/?post_type=isitwp_plugin&p=838";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:661:"<p>Are you looking to cut down on spam emails from your WordPress site, or send email via Gmail or Google Apps from your website? Take a look at the WP Mail SMTP plugin, which forces the WordPress wp_mail() function to use SMTP instead of the PHP mail() function. In our WP Mail SMTP review, you’ll find out how this plugin can help you send email from your WordPress site on your own terms.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.isitwp.com/wordpress-plugins/wp-mail-smtp/">WP Mail SMTP Review: #1 SMTP Plugin for WordPress</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.isitwp.com">IsItWP - WordPress Technology Lookup Tool</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Shahzad Saeed";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8285:"<p>Are you looking to cut down on spam emails from your WordPress site, or how to send emails via Gmail or Google Apps from your website? Take a look at the WP Mail SMTP plugin. It forces the WordPress wp_mail() function to use SMTP instead of the PHP mail() function. In our WP Mail SMTP review, you’ll find out how this plugin can help you send emails from your WordPress site on your own terms.</p>\n<p><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-mail-smtp/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><img src="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/wp-mail-smtp.png" alt="wp mail smtp plugin" width="775" height="350" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-224880" srcset="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/wp-mail-smtp.png 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/wp-mail-smtp-300x135.png 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/wp-mail-smtp-768x347.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px" /></a></p>\n<h2>How the wp_mail() Function Works in WordPress</h2>\n<p>As a WordPress user, you receive a lot of mail from your <a href="https://www.isitwp.com/how-to-make-a-website-step-by-step/">WordPress website</a>. Whenever a reader posts a comment, a post gets a pingback, or an <a title="How to Disable Automatic Updates in WordPress" href="http://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/how-to-disable-automatic-updates-in-wordpress/" target="_blank">update</a> is ready for your approval, WordPress automatically sends an email to notify you. You might get notification emails from your themes and plugins as well.</p>\n<p>Behind the scenes, these emails are all sent using a built-in WordPress function: wp_mail().</p>\n<p>The wp_mail() function uses the PHP function mail() to send emails from your website.</p>\n<h2>The Problem With the mail() Function</h2>\n<p>The mail() function is a built-in, default PHP function that enables sending emails.</p>\n<p>It’s a very simple, easy to use function, but can actually be a big problem.</p>\n<p>The mail() function is easy for <a title="Prevent Email Spam with WordPress AntiSpamBot Function" href="http://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/prevent-email-spam-with-wordpress-antispambot-function/" target="_blank">spammers</a> to take advantage of, hijacking it to send hundreds of emails through your website.</p>\n<p>In fact, it’s so notoriously hackable that some hosts have even disabled the use of the mail() function altogether.</p>\n<h2>Why You Need the WP Mail SMTP Plugin</h2>\n<p><a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-mail-smtp/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">The WP Mail SMTP plugin</a> works by bypassing the WordPress wp_mail() function and forcing it to use your SMTP settings. This means that you can set it to use whatever email you want, just by entering your SMTP options in the dashboard.</p>\n<p>Because of the mail() function’s vulnerability to hijacking, the WP Mail SMTP plugin can help keep your site safe. If a lot of spam emails are being sent from your website, you could get in trouble with your hosting company or get your site blacklisted.</p>\n<p>WP Mail SMTP can also come in handy when:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>your hosting company has disabled the mail() function and <a title="How to Fix WordPress Not Sending Email Issue" href="http://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/how-to-fix-wordpress-not-sending-email-issue/" target="_blank">WordPress can’t send email</a></li>\n<li>your web host’s settings are interfering with the delivery of mail from your WordPress site</li>\n<li>emails sent from your WordPress website always end up in the spam folder of recipients</li>\n<li>you want to set up WordPress to <a title="How to Send Email in WordPress using the Gmail SMTP Server" href="http://www.wpbeginner.com/plugins/how-to-send-email-in-wordpress-using-the-gmail-smtp-server/" target="_blank">send email via Gmail</a> or Google Apps (more on that below)</li>\n<li>messages sent via your <a title="Drag and Drop WordPress Form Builder" href="https://www.isitwp.com/best-wordpress-contact-form-plugins/">WordPress contact forms</a> never reach your inbox</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>How to Set Up WP Mail SMTP</h2>\n<p>After activating the plugin, head over to <strong>Settings » WP Mail SMTP</strong>. You’ll be asked to specify your from-email and name.</p>\n<p><img src="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/wp-mail-smtp-setting.png" alt="wp mail smtp settings" width="740" height="534" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-224884" srcset="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/wp-mail-smtp-setting.png 740w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/wp-mail-smtp-setting-300x216.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 740px) 100vw, 740px" /></p>\n<p>Then, you’ll be prompted to choose a mailer option.</p>\n<p>Unlike other SMTP plugins, <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-mail-smtp/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">WP Mail SMTP</a> allows you to set up SMTP on your site using 4 different mailer options:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Gmail or G Suite</li>\n<li>Mailgun</li>\n<li>SendGrid</li>\n<li>Other SMTP</li>\n</ul>\n<p><img src="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/wp-mail-smtp-mailer-options.png" alt="wp mail smtp mailer options" width="690" height="244" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-224883" srcset="https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/wp-mail-smtp-mailer-options.png 690w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/wp-mail-smtp-mailer-options-300x106.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 690px) 100vw, 690px" /></p>\n<p><strong>Gmail SMTP</strong></p>\n<p>Gmail SMTP allows you to use your Gmail or G Suite account for SMTP emails. The WP Mail SMTP plugin uses OAuth to authenticate your Google account, keeping your login information 100% secure.</p>\n<p><strong>Mailgun SMTP</strong></p>\n<p>Mailgun is a popular SMTP service provider that allows you to send large quantities of emails. WP Mail SMTP offers native integration with Mailgun.</p>\n<p>Mailgun works with any email account and is highly secure but requires a subscription.</p>\n<p><strong>SendGrid SMTP</strong></p>\n<p>SendGrid is yet another SMTP service provider, which is trusted by over 58,000 paying customers. WP Mail SMTP offers native integration with SendGrid as well.</p>\n<p>Just like Mailgun, SendGrid also works with any email account and is highly secure but requires a subscription.</p>\n<p><strong>Other SMTP </strong></p>\n<p>Other SMTP works with all major email services, including Gmail, Yahoo, Outlook, Microsoft Live, etc. With this option, you’ll have to insert your password in your wp-config.php file, so it’s not visible in your WordPress settings.</p>\n<p>Though Other SMTP is the least secure option, it could be the right choice for you if you need a solution that doesn’t require a third-party subscription.</p>\n<p>You can send a test email by clicking the Email Test tab. If anything goes wrong with your test email, the plugin will give you a detailed error message you can use for troubleshooting.</p>\n<h2>Support and Documentation</h2>\n<p>WP Mail SMTP is one of the most popular plugins in the WordPress.org directory, and is rated very highly.</p>\n<p>After being acquired by WPForms, it&#8217;s frequently updated and support is offered in a timely manner. </p>\n<p>Documentation is limited to basic troubleshooting for the most common errors. This plugin seems to be best suited for more tech-savvy users who&#8217;re already familiar with email settings.</p>\n<h2>Our Verdict on Using WP Mail SMTP on Your Site</h2>\n<p>With over a million installations on WordPress sites around the web, and an average 4.6 rating on the WordPress.org plugin directory, <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-mail-smtp/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">WP Mail SMTP</a> is a good choice for most users who need to send mail with SMTP from their WordPress site.</p>\n<p>We believe that this plugin is very helpful for any user having problems with mail delivery from their WordPress site.</p>\n<p>We give WP Mail SMTP 5 out of 5 stars. Here&#8217;s the breakdown of our review scores:</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.isitwp.com/wordpress-plugins/wp-mail-smtp/">WP Mail SMTP Review: #1 SMTP Plugin for WordPress</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.isitwp.com">IsItWP - WordPress Technology Lookup Tool</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:59:"https://www.isitwp.com/wordpress-plugins/wp-mail-smtp/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:54:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:61:"Top 100+ Black Friday &amp; Cyber Monday WordPress Deals 2018";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:65:"https://www.isitwp.com/black-friday-cyber-monday-wordpress-deals/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:73:"https://www.isitwp.com/black-friday-cyber-monday-wordpress-deals/#respond";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 20 Nov 2